subSubSection.paragraph:
Remarks:
There are no diagnostic morphological characters for this subgenus (
Reid 2002a
). Most have a strong black-and-white shell colour pattern. There is usually not only a basal white band within the aperture, but also another white band at the shoulder, and this is rare elsewhere in the genus (only in some Indo-West Pacific species of the 

E. (Granulilittorina) leucosticta

group; 
Reid 2007
); however, this second band is not always visible in the small members of the 

E. (Amerolittorina) porcata

group (
Reid 2002b
).
